Definition: a Jewish sect that recognizes only the Hebrew Scriptures as the source of divinely inspired legislation and denies the authority of the postbiblical tradition of the Talmud
Example: the sect arose in Iraq in the eighth century
Synonyms: sect, a, Jewish, that, recognizes, only, the, Hebrew, Scriptures, as, source, of, divinely, inspired, legislation, and, denies, authority, postbiblical, tradition, Talmud, arose, in, Iraq, eighth, century
Category: noun.group
